Miles: Thank you.

00:00:44.760 --> 00:00:48.400
Monty: RWBY as a show, it needs to be a very unique blend of

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:53.440
fantasy and reality, but to keep it slightly above normal design I often add

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:57.400
just a-- a touch of fantasy to them, so it very often lands into, like,

00:00:57.480 --> 00:01:01.220
um...contemporary or modern design plus.

00:01:01.280 --> 00:01:06.080
Having a winner for the Velvet design contest, we knew that it would be subtle changes

00:01:06.080 --> 00:01:08.400
that will compliment her weapon, compliment the rest of her team.

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:10.760
It really works for her 'cause it's very simple.

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:14.640
It's very nice, like, she has the bits of armor and stuff on her that denounce battle

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:16.800
but she's still...delicate, I guess is the way I'd put it.

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:18.640
Velvet's actually a mage

00:01:18.640 --> 00:01:23.060
so it makes sense to have that elvish kind of armor to her, that fancy, but

00:01:23.060 --> 00:01:25.100
dainty, delicate kind of armor to her.

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:29.340
So it really lends well to her character. Nobody else in the kingdom has an outfit like this.

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:34.260
The only thing we change is the color, 'cause we wanted to have a warmer air about her

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:36.400
so we changed it from green to a brown.

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:38.500
Monty: In considering the rest of her team

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:40.940
I needed something that matched it more, and also

00:01:40.940 --> 00:01:45.180
although I really like the original color scheme, it...it was a little too bright for her.

00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:51.780
We can build on simplicity, we can make-- and if that simplicity, in the beginning, is great

00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:53.880
then there's very little that we do with it.

00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:58.940
Monty: It can-- it sustains these minor changes that none of the designers could've anticipated

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:02.200
it's like we know what the character is, we know where we want it to go, we know what she wields.

00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:05.520
Yeah, we loved where it was going, so it was just taking us to go

00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:09.700
"alright, what can we do to just push it just a bit more to make her what we think of Velvet

00:02:09.700 --> 00:02:11.460
and what we think she's gonna be."

00:02:11.460 --> 00:02:15.700
So next up we'll be taking this process into actually making the 3D model

00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:18.200
which I'm actually-- it's happening right over there.

00:02:18.200 --> 00:02:21.500
Right now I'm working on the Velvet model.

00:02:21.500 --> 00:02:25.280
We get a concept for the character, though most of it's already there for us

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:27.420
and we just have to translate that into 3D

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:31.740
but it's a 2D image, so when we bring that into 3D we have to make sure that from every angle

00:02:31.740 --> 00:02:33.400
that character comes through.

00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:37.140
Now that I've layed out all the polygons onto a flat surface

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:40.780
I'm...coloring those polygons in Photoshop.

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:48.660
This screen here is...shows like all the polygons layed out flat and organized into a square texture

00:02:48.660 --> 00:02:53.180
'cause each one of those polygons on the flat surface represents a polygon on the 3D model

00:02:53.180 --> 00:02:59.380
that way I can just paint on in a flat image and that'll transfer over to the 3d model

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:04.200
and it'll take all the color information from that texture, that flat texture

00:03:04.200 --> 00:03:06.080
and show it on the 3D model.

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:10.200
When you look at a design, you have to take into consideration the fact that this person

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:11.560
will also be moving.

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:16.300
Even-- I'd even say to the non-winners of the Velvet design contest, there weren't losers.

00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:19.380
There were a lot of winners among them, but there can only be one we choose.

