My job is to model and texture anything that

00:05:59.840 --> 00:06:02.640
that doesn't have to do with characters or creatures

00:06:02.840 --> 00:06:06.280
so, basically all buildings, some of the vehicles.

00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:10.900
RWBY hits a very unique note where it's an animated show where everything's done in 3D

00:06:10.900 --> 00:06:17.340
so I kinda have to, like, find an area where the art can actually sustain the concept.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:19.820
Just communicate very-- very simply

00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:22.600
Monty: Yeah
Kristina: not too much distraction in the background

00:06:22.600 --> 00:06:26.220
'cause I like to-- in my environment I like to communicate more with just silhouettes and shapes.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:36.580
The thing that I understood from his less-is-more type design is that, in RWBY

00:06:36.580 --> 00:06:40.020
it's very...a flat, but very colorful type of show.

00:06:40.060 --> 00:06:45.660
It's not simplistic. In texture-wise, there's no real textures, it's mostly like gradients

00:06:45.660 --> 00:06:47.800
and that kinda good stuff so you get all these really

00:06:48.100 --> 00:06:53.540
...I guess the word for it is emotional, kind of colors to the show, or into each setting?

